    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** pacing the offense as our highest-rated option at 62.11. Despite a challenging matchup against Juan Mejia, **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a strong platoon advantage and a premium #2 spot in the order, providing the best floor-to-ceiling profile in our lineup. **Gary Sanchez** also earns a strong 59.74 start; his massive 10% boost from the SP skill projection against Patrick Corbin makes him a pivot-point play, as he looks to exploit the vulnerability of a lefty starter who struggles against his profile. Meanwhile, **Junior Caminero** remains a staple at 58.12, and while his SP skill adjustment is slightly penalized by Jordan Leasure\u2019s 3.44 xERA, his spot in the #2 hole continues to provide the volume necessary to remain a locked-in start.\n\nWe have navigated several platoon-heavy decisions, most notably with **Dillon Dingler** (56.11), who receives a significant +14% dynamic boost against Kris Bubic. This puts him well ahead of other options, even as we remain cautious regarding the pending official lineup confirmation. The most difficult bench decision involved **Josh Smith**, who finished at 39.52. While **Josh Smith** carried a +10% park factor, his negative 15% platoon adjustment against Jacob Lopez ultimately made him unstartable compared to our core starters. We are also keeping a watchful eye on **Jerar Encarnacion** (35.72), who was excluded due to a combination of a low-value #8 batting order projection and a 34% rain risk against Chase Burns, which could easily turn a marginal start into a complete loss of efficiency. As we look at the remainder of our roster, **Trea Turner**, **Christian Yelich**, **Caleb Durbin**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Carson Benge**, **Victor Scott II**, **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, and **Luis Pena** will remain on standby as we manage our daily game caps to protect our long-term category upside.",
